{{Infobox journal | title = African Human Rights Law Reports | cover = | discipline = [[International human rights law|Human rights law]] | abbreviation = Afr. Hum. Rights Law Rep. | language = English, French | editor = Christof Heyns | publisher = JUTA Law on behalf of the [[Centre for Human Rights]] ([[University of Pretoria]]) | country = South Africa | history = 2001-present | frequency = Annually | openaccess = Yes | website = http://www1.chr.up.ac.za/index.php/publications/ahrlr.html | link1 = https://web.archive.org/web/20110221084421/http://www.chr.up.ac.za:80/index.php/ahrlj-downloads.html | link1-name = Online access | ISSN = | eISSN = 1812-2418 | JSTOR = | OCLC = 63788369 | LCCN = }} The '''''African Human Rights Law Reports''''' is an annual [[law review|law journal]] published by JUTA Law on behalf of the [[Centre for Human Rights]] at the [[University of Pretoria]]. It contains legal decisions of relevance to [[international human rights law|human rights law]] in Africa. These include selected domestic decisions from the whole continent, as well as the decisions of the [[African Commission on Human and Peoples' Rights]] and the [[United Nations]] treaty bodies, dealing with [[List of sovereign states and dependent territories in Africa|African countries]]. It is published in English and French and is indexed in the [[International Bibliography of the Social Sciences]].
