A '''landlocked parcel''' is a [[land lot|real estate plot]] that has no [[right of way]] to a public roadway.<ref>[http://homeguides.sfgate.com/landlocked-mean-7864.html What Does Landlocked Mean?], SFGate</ref> A landlocked parcel has less value than a parcel that is not landlocked.<ref>[https://www.sapling.com/8668242/landlocked-property-worth What Is Landlocked Property Worth?], Sapling</ref> The owner of a landlocked parcel can obtain access to a public roadway by [[easement]].<ref>[http://blog.landcentral.com/land-university-blog/landlocked-property-investing/#.WII5YPkrK0k Who Would Ever Want A Landlocked Property?], landcentral</ref>
